cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically with motion compensation for rolling shutter cameras in vehicles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the Ackermann motion model, which is a common model used in robotics, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The proposed method uses a minimal solver, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves geometric reasoning and estimation, which could fall under cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
